Sergeant Norman Turgel, 24, and Gena, 20, were married two months before the liberation of the notorious Bergen-Belsen camp in 1945 .
Norman became so besotted with Gena that he proposed to Gena one day .
The couple were forced into hiding in secret rooms hidden inside Otto Frank's office building .
In 1945, Anne Frank's diaries of persecution at the hands of the Nazis became world-famous .